cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.PF, cs.NI, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with large-scale distributed compute systems and job scheduling. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses the management of stragglers, which can be seen as a control problem. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper aims to improve the performance of distributed compute systems. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) may be relevant as distributed compute systems often rely on network communication. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) may be relevant as the paper discusses the computation of job completion time and cost, which involves algorithmic analysis.
